00:32:04.650 --> 00:32:08.240
But once we get this concept
of prefers-reduced-data,

00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:10.950
we could have three
steps in our motion,

00:32:10.950 --> 00:32:15.060
which would be the default,
a reduced one, which has a little bit

00:32:15.060 --> 00:32:17.220
of movement, but very small.

00:32:17.220 --> 00:32:19.740
And then you could use
the prefers-reduced-data

00:32:19.740 --> 00:32:22.880
to actually remove all
the motion together.

00:32:22.880 --> 00:32:25.980
So this GIF is not broken;
it's just a still-shot,

00:32:25.980 --> 00:32:29.160
because nothing has happened
on the prefers-reduced-data.

00:32:30.620 --> 00:32:35.190
So again, very much like other
media queries, prefers-reduced-data,

00:32:35.190 --> 00:32:36.820
reduce.

00:32:36.820 --> 00:32:41.540
In this case, I had no
animation, nothing is happening.

00:32:41.540 --> 00:32:43.940
Unfortunately,
this is zero all the way.

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:45.520
Tons and tons of flags.

00:32:45.520 --> 00:32:47.630
That means it's good,
it means it's experimental,

00:32:47.630 --> 00:32:50.430
that means that maybe
