00:33:28.470 --> 00:33:32.990
Just a quick recap, we have the
color: prefers-colors-scheme,

00:33:32.990 --> 00:33:35.980
forced-colors, and inverted colors.

00:33:35.980 --> 00:33:38.626
We have the contrast,
which is prefers-contrast,

00:33:38.627 --> 00:33:40.030
and reduced transparency.

00:33:41.232 --> 00:33:43.356
For motion,
we have prefers-reduced-motion,

00:33:43.357 --> 00:33:44.612
and prefers-reduced-data.

00:33:45.740 --> 00:33:50.770
If you're using none of these things,
we're having zero user choices.

00:33:50.770 --> 00:33:55.010
You're saying, I know all
about your user experience

00:33:55.010 --> 00:34:00.130
and I am giving you zero
options, which is, let's face it,

00:34:00.130 --> 00:34:02.090
most sites that we go to, right?

00:34:03.230 --> 00:34:08.230
If we incorporate even the
three that are most supported...

00:34:08.230 --> 00:34:11.300
I was counting that
as 90% or higher ...

00:34:11.300 --> 00:34:15.590
That gives your users a
combination of 16 choices.

00:34:15.590 --> 00:34:18.460
It's an exponential thing
because you have multiple choices

00:34:18.460 --> 00:34:21.620
under each different category.

00:34:21.620 --> 00:34:23.460
For two of the categories,
you only have two options;

00:34:23.460 --> 00:34:26.210
but the one color contrast,
you have four, so it equals

00:34:26.210 --> 00:34:28.970
to 16 user choices.

00:34:28.970 --> 00:34:32.130
There's that one, that
forced-colors, it's, like, at 87%.

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:36.980
So in the future, this would be even
32 choices, which is pretty cool.

00:34:38.370 --> 00:34:41.740
But if we think about the
future, we dream about the future

00:34:41.740 --> 00:34:45.970
with browsers and operating systems
settings all supporting all of these,

00:34:45.970 --> 00:34:49.690
we have a staggering 256 options.

00:34:49.690 --> 00:34:51.560
With just adding
those, what do we have?

00:34:51.560 --> 00:34:57.040
Three, four, five, six,
seven media features?

00:34:57.040 --> 00:34:59.410
So it's pretty exciting.

00:34:59.410 --> 00:35:01.680
So lots of different options.

00:35:01.680 --> 00:35:07.240
Again, there are some things that
can conflict, but this is minimum

00:35:07.240 --> 00:35:10.280
if you had each of them,
because you can also combine things

00:35:10.280 --> 00:35:12.690
to create brand new scenarios.

00:35:12.690 --> 00:35:14.960
So you could have a
prefers-reduced-motion

00:35:14.960 --> 00:35:18.650
just for light,
prefers-reduced-motion just for dark.

00:35:18.650 --> 00:35:23.370
You can imagine the combinations can
extend beyond just those simple ones.

00:35:23.370 --> 00:35:24.890
So this would be a simple number.

00:35:24.890 --> 00:35:29.930
So the number really could go on
to infinity, if we’re being honest.

00:35:29.930 --> 00:35:32.120
So pretty exciting.

00:35:32.120 --> 00:35:33.000
I'm excited about it.

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:34.770
I hope I got you a
little bit excited.

00:35:34.770 --> 00:35:37.670
Maybe you saw some things
that you hadn't seen before.

00:35:37.670 --> 00:35:41.577
But really, this concept
of digital accessibility

00:35:41.578 --> 00:35:43.530
sometimes gets a bad rap

00:35:43.530 --> 00:35:47.530
in our technical digital world,
because people are worried

00:35:47.530 --> 00:35:51.280
about beautiful design,
and cutting-edge functionality.

00:35:51.280 --> 00:35:53.850
But hopefully, we saw today that
it doesn't have to be the case.

00:35:53.850 --> 00:35:55.940
You don't have to
choose one or the other.

00:35:55.940 --> 00:35:59.580
You can customize it,
offer your users choices

00:35:59.580 --> 00:36:02.760
to customize their experience and
include all those amazing things

00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:04.850
and cutting-edge things
you want to think of,

00:36:04.850 --> 00:36:07.360
but then you're also giving it
to them in a responsible way.

00:36:08.550 --> 00:36:11.950
As professionals in the technology
industry, we really should aim

00:36:11.950 --> 00:36:15.320
to make our digital projects
accessible, and offer choices

00:36:15.320 --> 00:36:18.250
to each individual to
customize their experience.

00:36:18.250 --> 00:36:21.670
Our job is to provide options,
and then let the people choose

00:36:21.670 --> 00:36:22.670
their own adventure.

